320
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:26,440
I called him so many times, he wouldn’t answer.

321
00:33:28,640 --> 00:33:31,040
He probably had something to do.

322
00:33:36,400 --> 00:33:38,640
Let me borrow your phone, I’ll call him.

323
00:33:41,560 --> 00:33:45,440
Damn, what the hell’s with you today? You’re so annoying.

324
00:33:46,520 --> 00:33:49,160
Just let me borrow it.

325
00:33:53,280 --> 00:33:54,120
Fine.

326
00:34:03,040 --> 00:34:03,920
Hello, Champ.

327
00:34:05,400 --> 00:34:06,920
Why aren’t you answering my calls?

328
00:34:07,400 --> 00:34:08,639
Are you ignoring me now?

329
00:34:08,719 --> 00:34:10,960
Sorn, I gotta go.

330
00:34:11,440 --> 00:34:15,280
Don’t hang up on me, Jun! How are we supposed to fix this if you keep running away?

331
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:23,719
I know you’re mad, but I want to talk, I want to clear things up. If you keep avoiding me, how can we fix it?

332
00:34:25,159 --> 00:34:26,560
Let’s talk later.

333
00:34:34,480 --> 00:34:35,440
Jun.

334
00:34:37,719 --> 00:34:40,800
I’ll come pick you up this evening. You’re at Tai’s place, right?

335
00:34:41,840 --> 00:34:44,360
