336
00:34:45,840 --> 00:34:47,400
Up to you.

337
00:34:48,520 --> 00:34:50,239
See you.

338
00:35:05,840 --> 00:35:06,720
Champ.

339
00:35:08,360 --> 00:35:12,080
What’s wrong with Sorn lately? Did he fight with his girlfriend?

340
00:35:13,200 --> 00:35:15,520
No idea, maybe he’s on his period.

341
00:35:15,520 --> 00:35:18,640
Oh, his period?

342
00:35:19,840 --> 00:35:23,760
Just like me, mine just started too.

343
00:35:24,400 --> 00:35:30,080
I’ll go buy pads then, maybe get some for Sorn too. The winged ones.

344
00:35:30,080 --> 00:35:32,640
Size 20. Byeee.

345
00:35:44,960 --> 00:35:48,840
Hey, what are you eating? Having a celebration without telling me?

346
00:35:48,840 --> 00:35:50,360
Why are you here?

347
00:35:54,080 --> 00:35:55,000
Where is he?

348
00:35:55,000 --> 00:35:56,000
Who?

349
00:35:57,840 --> 00:36:03,000
Don’t play dumb. I know you know everything. I want to talk to him first.

350
00:36:05,480 --> 00:36:06,840
Where are you going?

351
00:36:12,120 --> 00:36:17,080
If you won’t help, then shut up. I’ll go look for him.

352
00:36:18,200 --> 00:36:23,080
If I do shut up, will you calm down?

353
00:36:25,400 --> 00:36:27,960
Or will you finally be clearer than Jun is?

354
00:36:30,000 --> 00:36:34,840
You led the kid on for months, dragged me into it until you started lying to yourself too.

355
00:36:36,000 --> 00:36:41,480
And when the kid actually fell for you, you turned out to be a coward.

356
00:36:46,880 --> 00:36:53,000
Have you even asked yourself whether you really like him?

357
00:36:55,280 --> 00:36:59,160
Sorn, are you and Jun dating?

358
00:37:02,600 --> 00:37:04,080
Dating?, Damn!!!

359
00:37:06,520 --> 00:37:12,080
He doesn’t even know if he really likes Jun.

360
00:37:18,480 --> 00:37:25,000
Then how can I admit I like him? He’s your little brother.

361
00:37:26,960 --> 00:37:28,800
I had to hold myself back.

362
00:37:31,040 --> 00:37:32,160
Because if you get mad…

363
00:37:37,280 --> 00:37:44,400
So how many times have you two done it? Did you ever think that
he’s my little brother?

364
00:37:47,400 --> 00:37:51,680
If you don’t really like him, then let him go.

365
00:37:56,160 --> 00:37:58,000
Don’t let him fall deeper than he already has.

366
00:37:59,160 --> 00:38:01,760
Guys, calm down!

367
00:38:03,640 --> 00:38:08,040
Where’s Jun? Let’s just call him and talk this out.

368
00:38:14,280 --> 00:38:15,960
Jun’s not here.

369
00:38:25,000 --> 00:38:26,520
Tai.

370
00:38:29,160 --> 00:38:30,480
I want to talk to Jun.

371
00:38:32,200 --> 00:38:36,760
Then why didn’t you talk to him before?

372
00:38:39,360 --> 00:38:48,760
Think hard—what did you say to him that made him not want to face you?

373
00:38:50,160 --> 00:38:57,800
Let me tell you something. First thing you need to do is admit your own damn feelings.

374
00:39:00,720 --> 00:39:02,120
You idiot!!!

375
00:39:09,280 --> 00:39:14,040
Fine… I like him.

376
00:39:17,320 --> 00:39:19,960
I like them… so much it hurts.

377
00:39:26,640 --> 00:39:27,960
I don’t usually go for younger people, you know...

378
00:39:38,520 --> 00:39:40,320
But I like them. I really do.

379
00:40:16,520 --> 00:40:19,760
So no one thought to tell me anything?

380
00:40:23,400 --> 00:40:27,880
It’s Sorn business, not yours.

381
00:40:35,400 --> 00:40:41,120
Fine… I get it.

382
00:41:04,160 --> 00:41:09,800
Sorn? You’re here late. Is something wrong? Did something happen to Jun?

383
00:41:13,560 --> 00:41:22,720
Oh, no. I just happened to be nearby. Jun asked me to bring something he forgot, but he messaged me saying I don’t need to anymore.

384
00:41:25,400 --> 00:41:27,000
Well then, I’ll get going.

385
00:41:30,200 --> 00:41:31,560
Okay, take care getting home.

386
00:42:35,520 --> 00:42:40,040
Why do I feel like I’m helping someone run off with someone else’s wife?

387
00:42:52,400 --> 00:42:57,680
You’re still not answering Sorn’s calls? He’s called you so many times.

388
00:42:59,480 --> 00:43:02,040
Screw it. Just ignore it.

389
00:43:06,760 --> 00:43:09,600
Shit, he’s calling my house now.

390
00:43:12,880 --> 00:43:20,160
Just pick up. But don’t tell him I’m with you. And if he asks where I am, don’t say anything.

391
00:43:22,400 --> 00:43:27,120
Hello, bro. I can’t say, Tai orders.

392
00:43:30,480 --> 00:43:36,520
That’s all for now, my dad asked me to run an errand. Yes, sir.

393
00:43:43,840 --> 00:43:49,840
Jun, what are you gonna do if he actually finds you?

394
00:43:57,960 --> 00:44:00,200
I don’t know.

395
00:44:00,200 --> 00:44:03,280
Then… let me ask you this instead.

396
00:44:05,440 --> 00:44:12,360
If he tells you he likes you… would you be with him?

397
00:44:33,720 --> 00:44:36,240
What would you like to order today, P’James?

398
00:44:36,240 --> 00:44:38,920
Espresso, thanks.

399
00:44:41,480 --> 00:44:45,040
Morning, P’Sorn! You’re here early today.

400
00:44:45,040 --> 00:44:46,640
Good morning, P’Sorn.

401
00:44:50,640 --> 00:44:53,520
Mmm... Jun’s not coming in to work today?

402
00:44:53,520 --> 00:44:56,080
Looks like… he’s not coming.

403
00:44:59,800 --> 00:45:02,080
Why does Sorn look so stressed today?

404
00:45:02,080 --> 00:45:04,160
Yeah, I’m kinda scared now too.

405
00:45:04,440 --> 00:45:05,840
You can't avoid me forever, Jun.

406
00:45:05,840 --> 00:45:06,880
I will find you.

407
00:45:06,880 --> 00:45:08,760
Get ready to meet me.

408
00:45:22,320 --> 00:45:28,200
Hey, have you and Jun talked it out yet?

409
00:45:32,880 --> 00:45:38,640
He’s avoiding me. Thinks he can just take leave and disappear.

410
00:45:40,440 --> 00:45:42,160
So what are you gonna do?

411
00:45:44,200 --> 00:45:45,720
He can’t stay off work for long.

412
00:45:46,840 --> 00:45:50,280
If he’s gone too much, he won’t pass his internship.

413
00:46:19,840 --> 00:46:24,160
Look… about yesterday, I’m sorry.

414
00:46:28,680 --> 00:46:31,240
I didn’t mean to go off on you like that.

415
00:46:34,280 --> 00:46:38,600
But you were right. It’s not really my business.

416
00:46:45,920 --> 00:46:47,720
Who says that?

417
00:46:51,480 --> 00:46:53,760
Everything’s your business too…

418
00:46:59,400 --> 00:47:04,280
But why… I don’t feel like that.

419
00:47:09,200 --> 00:47:13,440
What even are we? I don’t even know.

420
00:47:19,080 --> 00:47:20,320
Forget it…

421
00:47:21,120 --> 00:47:24,800
Hey, it’s not like that…

422
00:47:34,480 --> 00:47:39,720
If you don’t really feel anything, then don’t act like this.

423
00:47:57,400 --> 00:48:00,040
Yo Win, doing stock check?

424
00:48:00,040 --> 00:48:02,040
Yeah… so much stuff.

425
00:48:03,440 --> 00:48:06,480
Hey, let’s grab something to eat tonight. I’m starving.

426
00:48:07,320 --> 00:48:09,080
Pad Thai with omelette sound good?

427
00:48:09,080 --> 00:48:11,240
You got it, man.

428
00:48:11,240 --> 00:48:13,480
You made a deal. No backing out.

429
00:48:13,480 --> 00:48:14,080
Deal!

430
00:48:14,080 --> 00:48:16,280
See you, back to work.

431
00:48:16,280 --> 00:48:18,280
Bye. Work hard, man.

432
00:48:18,280 --> 00:48:19,120
Okay.

433
00:48:37,560 --> 00:48:39,640
Still mad at me?

434
00:48:39,640 --> 00:48:42,360
What… Who’s mad at you?

435
00:48:44,080 --> 00:48:49,240
Can we not be like this? I really hate this feeling.

436
00:48:51,200 --> 00:48:57,000
You don’t need to feel anything. It’s always left hanging anyway.

437
00:48:58,600 --> 00:48:59,400
Champ...

438
00:49:01,120 --> 00:49:02,080
It’s just...

439
00:49:02,080 --> 00:49:05,400
It’s fine. It’s not even my business.

440
00:49:06,840 --> 00:49:11,040
Champ, talk nicely to me, please?

441
00:49:16,680 --> 00:49:17,680
Alright then, truce.

442
00:50:03,880 --> 00:50:05,560
You look kinda cute in glasses, y’know.

443
00:50:07,600 --> 00:50:09,160
Don’t even.

444
00:50:13,640 --> 00:50:15,800
Still mad? Huh?

445
00:50:17,520 --> 00:50:18,800
Dunno.

446
00:50:40,720 --> 00:50:42,760
Do you even shower, dude?

447
00:50:43,000 --> 00:50:43,840
Mmm…

448
00:50:46,720 --> 00:50:51,080
In the meantime, you should really think about your feelings.

449
00:50:54,200 --> 00:50:55,480
Mmm…

450
00:50:57,000 --> 00:50:59,560
Maybe Jun needs time too.

451
00:51:01,560 --> 00:51:07,720
He’s been gone for a whole week. Still not enough time to think things through?

452
00:51:26,440 --> 00:51:29,000
Damn, shave that thing already!

453
00:51:30,840 --> 00:51:32,360
Dude, I legit thought you were a jungle bandit.

454
00:51:36,200 --> 00:51:37,440
What are we celebrating?

455
00:51:38,840 --> 00:51:42,480
Celebrate my ass. I came to comfort someone heartbroken.

456
00:51:44,880 --> 00:51:45,760
Who?

457
00:51:46,640 --> 00:51:47,760
You, idiot.

458
00:51:49,160 --> 00:51:50,160
I’m not heartbroken.

459
00:51:51,280 --> 00:51:52,240
I just…

460
00:51:52,240 --> 00:51:53,320
Got dumped?

461
00:52:00,720 --> 00:52:06,080
I asked Korn where Jun is—he didn’t know.

462
00:52:06,920 --> 00:52:10,200
Asked Tai—he wouldn’t say a word.

463
00:52:12,240 --> 00:52:20,200
But that guy Jom, the one who went clubbing with Jun? He knows.

464
00:52:22,280 --> 00:52:24,800
Oh hey.

465
00:52:31,080 --> 00:52:33,040
Whose rhino plushie is that?

466
00:52:40,440 --> 00:52:42,040
